<!DOCTYPE concept PUBLIC "-//OASIS//DTD DITA Concept//EN" "concept.dtd" []>
<concept xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" id="internal-entity" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="urn:oasis:names:tc:dita:xsd:concept.xsd:1.1">
  <title>Internal Entity</title>
  <conbody id="body">
    <p id="internal-entity-intro"><?serna-redline-start 0 If some content is to be used multiple times within the single document, use internal entity.?>An <keyword>internal entity</keyword> can be reused only in the document in which it was declared.<?serna-redline-end?><fig frame="all">
        <title>Internal entity in the Editing Window and ContentMap.</title>
        <image href="internal-entity-in-the-editing-window-and-content-map.png" align="center" placement="break"/>
      </fig></p>
    <p>You can do the following operations with internal entities:<ul>
        <li>
          <p><xref href="converting-to-internal-entity.xml">
              <b>Convert a part of document content to an internal entity</b>
            </xref></p>
          <p conref="converting-to-internal-entity.xml#converting-to-internal-entity/convert-to-internal-entity-intro"/>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p><xref href="inserting-internal-entity.xml">
              <b>Insert an internal entity</b>
            </xref></p>
          <p conref="inserting-internal-entity.xml#inserting-internal-entity/insert-internal-entity-intro"/>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p><xref href="converting-from-internal-entity.xml">
              <b>Convert an internal entity to a regular content</b>
            </xref></p>
          <p conref="converting-from-internal-entity.xml#converting-from-internal-entity/convert-from-internal-entity-intro"/>
        </li>
      </ul></p>
  </conbody>
</concept>
